E.3 LTL Formulas in Lean (Excerpt)

We can encode LTL formulas as inductive types and define satisfaction. For brevity, we show a simplified version.

```lean
inductive LTL (AP : Type) where
  | atom (p : AP)
  | not (φ : LTL AP)
  | and (φ ψ : LTL AP)
  | next (φ : LTL AP)
  | until (φ ψ : LTL AP)

def eval (σ : Nat → Set AP) : LTL AP → Nat → Prop
  | atom p => fun i => p ∈ σ i
  | not φ => fun i => ¬ eval σ φ i
  | and φ ψ => fun i => eval σ φ i ∧ eval σ ψ i
  | next φ => fun i => eval σ φ (i+1)
  | until φ ψ => fun i => ∃ j ≥ i, eval σ ψ j ∧ ∀ k ∈ [i, j-1], eval σ φ k
```

